Name: colorutil
Synopsis: Utilities for parsing and manipulating colors.

Functions.Name: BenchmarkKelvinToColor
Functions.Comment:
This benchmark is here both to validate the speed, but also to ensure none of this
wild floating point math accumulates any noticable errors.

Functions.Name: Equals
Functions.Comment: Return whether two colors are equivalent in the 24-bit RGB (RGB255) color space.

Functions.Name: HslToRgb
Functions.Comment:
Given HSL values (where hue is given in degrees (out of 360°), saturation
and lightness are [0, 1]), return the corresponding RGB values (where each value
is [0, 255]).
Functions.Signature: HslToRgb(hue float64, saturation float64, lightness float64) (uint8, uint8, uint8)

Functions.Name: HsvToRgb
Functions.Comment:
Given HSL values (where hue is given in degrees (out of 360°), saturation
and value are [0, 1]), return the corresponding RGB values (where each value
is [0, 255]).
Functions.Signature: HsvToRgb(hue float64, saturation float64, value float64) (uint8, uint8, uint8)

Functions.Name: KelvinToColor
Functions.Comment:
Takes a color temperature in degrees Kelvin and returns a valid Color for that temperature.
This function works best between 1000K and 40000K.

Functions.Name: RgbToHsl
Functions.Comment:
Given RGB values (where each value is [0, 255]), return the hue (in degrees), saturation,
and lightness (where each is [0, 1]).
Functions.Signature: RgbToHsl(r float64, g float64, b float64) (float64, float64, float64)

Methods.Name: Equals
Methods.Comment: Return whether the given color is equal to this one in the 24-bit RGB (RGB255) color space

Methods.Name: HSI
Methods.Comment: Return the current color as hue (out of 360°), saturation [0, 1], and intensity [0, 1].

Methods.Name: HSL
Methods.Comment: Return the current color as hue (out of 360°), saturation [0, 1], and lightness [0, 1].

Methods.Name: HSV
Methods.Comment: Return the current color as hue (out of 360°), saturation [0, 1], and value [0, 1].

Methods.Name: NativeRGBA
Methods.Comment: Return the color as a color.RGBA struct.

Methods.Name: RGBA
Methods.Comment: Return the current color as a 32-bit uint quad, implementing the color.Color interface.

Methods.Name: RGBA255
Methods.Comment: Return the current color as 4x 8-bit RGB values, each [0, 255].

Methods.Name: MustParse
Methods.Comment: Parse the given value into a Color or panic.

Methods.Name: Parse
Methods.Comment: Parse the given value into a Color or return an error.

Methods.Name: Darken
Methods.Comment:
Darken the given color by a certain percent.  Consistent with the results of the
Sass darken() function.

Methods.Name: Lighten
Methods.Comment:
Lighten the given color by a certain percent.  Consistent with the results of the
Sass lighten() function.

Methods.Name: Saturate
Methods.Comment:
Saturate the given color by a certain percent.  Consistent with the results of the
Sass saturate() function.

Methods.Name: Desaturate
Methods.Comment:
Desaturate the given color by a certain percent.  Consistent with the results of the
Sass desaturate() function.

Methods.Name: AdjustHue
Methods.Comment: Adjust the hue of the given color by the specified number of degrees.

Methods.Name: MixN
Methods.Comment:
Mix two colors, producing a third.  The weight value specifies how much of the first color
should be included.  Consistent with the results of the Sass mix() function.
Methods.Signature: MixN(first interface{}, second interface{}, weight float64) (Color, error)

Methods.Name: Mix
Methods.Comment: Mix two colors in equal parts, producing a third.
